title: Makeshift memorial grows after car crash at Oklahoma parade
text: > Top News Makeshift memorial grows after car crash at Oklahoma parade Oklahoma State students Kelly Cooke, right, and Rebecca Buchanan read messages on a memorial in Stillwater, Okla., Saturday, Oct. 24, 2015, near where a car crashed into spectators during the Oklahoma State University homecoming parade killing multiple and injuring several others. (Sarah Phipps/The Oklahoman via AP) LOCAL STATIONS OUT (KFOR, KOCO, KWTV, KOKH, KAUT OUT); LOCAL WEBSITES OUT; LOCAL PRINT OUT (EDMOND SUN OUT, OKLAHOMA GAZETTE OUT) TABLOIDS OUT; MANDATORY CREDIT
